climbs.name: Sticky Monkey
climbs.fa: Gavin Emmons, Noal Elkins, Dennis Erik Strom 3/2016

content.description:
This is the first route you find at the end of the short approach trail. The route goes up the bulge following 7 bolts. Super fun pockets. Use a spotter or a stick clip getting to the first bolt - it's thin.

The bottom slab can stay wet after rain due to moss.
content.protection: 7 bolts. Chains w/hooks at the top.
content.location: First route you come to at the end of the approach trail. Left of the chimney.

climbs.name: Rug Burn
climbs.fa: Gavin Emmons, Noal Elkins, Dennis Erik Strom 7/2019

content.description: Up a vertical section, then rest, then a harder/fun upper bulge. Hard part is the technical stem moves up high. Shares an anchor with Cutting the Rug.
content.location: Last route on the left of the north side of Voyeur Wall before going around the corner.

climbs.name: O.C.D. Overdrive
climbs.fa: Noal Elkins, Dennis Erik Strom, John Cook, Jon Cochran 2/2016

content.description: Two pitches, 5.8 and 5.6. The first pitch is good (have not done the 2nd pitch).
content.location: Next route left from Sticky Monkey, just left of the approach trail.

content.description: Project. This is the first route to the left of Peephole Chimney. As of this writing it is 3 bolts. The line has not had much attention lately. Listing as the 3 bolts can confuse folks.
content.location: First bolts to the right of the Peephole Chimney

climbs.name: Cutting the Rug
climbs.fa: Gavin Emmons, Dennis Erik Strom, Noal Elkins 11/ 2015

content.description: Great climbing up a 5.8 ramp. Then up and over a well protected bulge to chains. Great rock!
content.location: About 80 feet left of where the approach trail meets the wall.
